If you label the home page of a space, it will show up in the NavMap as "Home". This is not very descriptive.
It seems reasonable that it should be given the name of the space as the title in the NavMap, and not "Home", right?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6457].
  {panel}

I think it would make sense to be able to (perhaps optionally) group the items in the NavMap based on the space that they belong to. You should probably also (again, perhaps optionally) add the name of the space as a label to the group.

Perhaps you chould also sort / color code items based on their hierarchy level (ie. top level pages get a different sort order / color than their child pages)?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6456].
  {panel}

It would be nice to indicate which sites you're interested in sending trackback pings to; as it stands, it's possible for Confluence to send more information than we might ideally desire.  

See CSP-4359 for reference.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6451].
  {panel}

If you delete a page, all the children become orphaned. If you restore a deleted page, the children stay orphaned.  I would be beneficial if you could restore the parent/child relationships on a page restore.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6448].
  {panel}

In version 2.1.5a I set my confluence site home page as one of my spaces - our companies home page - not the dashboard. Each of  our departments have their own space that they maintain information but, I am the admin. We have differenct color schemes for a few departments and which requires an new logo with that color scheme. So now, with the new "feature" of the logoblock going to the spaces home page and not the designated confluence defualt home page or the individuals default home page (which I thought was the reason behind indivuduals being able to set a home page in their profile). Several of my site are not linking back to my home page.

I feel that this should be up to the admin of the site to determine if the home page for each site needs to go back to the default home page or the sites home page. But, it should not override the individuals set home page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6446].
  {panel}

It would be nice if I could build a RSS feed that only includes my favourite pages.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6444].
  {panel}

We'd like to configure the way that search results look like. The search results page is pretty complex for our taste, especially if you want to skim through a lot of results. Offer for example a way to enable/disable the page content preview (so only the page name will be shown). All this should be on a per user basis (so the users can select the search result design the way they want)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6438].
  {panel}

Users who are not logged in can restrict still their searches to favourites on dosearchsite.action, despite not having any set. i couldn't see why no results were listed when I used a CAC quicksearch, since they are setup to search only favourites (to dodge the issue with being unable to search multiple spaces) and anonymous access means that it isn't very obvious when you are not actually logged in. 

Feel free to close as not a bug if you don't think anyone will run into this besides us CAC quicksearchers, otherwise it wold be nice to add a check that disables favourite searches for anonymous users and/or displays an option to login when a anonymous users searches them.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6417].
  {panel}

When listing news items, there is no intuitive UI for user to realise that each news item title is a click-able link. There should be a way of demonstrating the fact that to edit the news item, user is required to click the item's title. Perhaps highlighting the titles, or listing them separately may make it more obvious.

Please see related discussion at https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CSP-3207

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6404].
  {panel}

This is due to the mechanism we use for generating the people directory: it searches the Confluence index for user profile records. 

User profiles are only created when a user logs in for the first time.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6394].
  {panel}

Provide a navigation bar that shows the user's navigation history.  We have several users who have used other Wikis previously, and they have found this feature to be invaluable in being able to "retrace" their steps when moving through the Wiki.

Although your "History" pop-up has some of this functionality, it does have some problems.  If you leave the pop-up window open, the history is not dynamically updated as you navigate through the pages: you must click on the "History" button to update the contents of the pop-up.  Also, if you click on a link in the History pop-up, then the pop-up closes, which is frustrating if you're trying to retain the history window as your main form of backward navigation.

The lack of this feature in the product may force us to look elsewhere for our Wiki selection (we are currently in the evaluation stage).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6391].
  {panel}

Users complain about the nuisance of adding a link to files on mapped drives. They need to copy the path, change \ to /, get the file name and write the whole thing into [file://....]. This is far too complicated for lowpower users.

There is already a tab 'External link' in 'Insert Link'. Could we add a browse button for searching for documents?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6390].
  {panel}

It can be very usefull to have an abillity to switch confluence in read-only mode. During our last problems with database, which is hosted several application including Confluence and Jira, all mentioned services was unavailable. It is desirable to be able to run some kind of backup instance of Confluence in read-only mode: data can be searched and viewed, but not modified. This could decrease downtime during upgrade, too. 

Several members of our team really suffer, if they havn't loved wiki online. :-)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6378].
  {panel}

There is currently no way to view the historical contents of a page via the remote interface.  It would be nice if the getPageByVersion service were exposed on the SOAP and XMLRPC interfaces.  This will allow remote clients to create visual diffs of two versions like is currently done in the web UI.

Attached is a patch that adds a new service getPageByVersion to both the XMRPC and SOAP interfaces.  I was unable to test it as I couldn't get Confluence to run on my machine (possibly a Java6 issue)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6373].
  {panel}

Currently in confluence, there is no way to ensure that users enter comments to describe the purpose of their page edits.  This dilutes the value of the page history.  Our organization, and I'm sure many others, would like the option of making these page-edit comments mandatory *unless* the edit is marked as a "Minor change".  This would require users to add comments and simultaneously encourage them to use the "Minor change" checkbox when appropriate, thus reducing the amount of unnecessary notification emails and RSS.

I've marked this issue as Priority: Major due to the fact that it is a loss of potential functionality and that there exists no easy workaround (that I know of) to enable this kind of validation.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6372].
  {panel}

When a user attempts to upload an attachment but the file upload process fails, the counter on attachment page and associated information is updated as though the operation succeeded. The database entry is still being made despite upload attempt failing.

Checking the source code shows that the database entry is updated prior to the transfer being attempted to generate the id for the file-name, but if the upload fails then no rollback is performed on the database operation.

Improved behaviour would be to check the file upload success and undo the entry if the attempt was unsuccessful.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6369].
  {panel}

We can add data items to the Dynamic Tasklist macro and see them. But if we revisit the page with Dynamic Tasklist macro after clicking on other pages then we can not see the data items in the Dynamic Tasklist Macro. But we can see them again if we refresh the page manually.

