{noformat}
The automatic anchors created for the headers aren't always unique.

h1. Introduction
h2. Test Case 1
h3. Conclusions
h2. Test Case 2
h3. Conclusions

There is no way to accuratly link to the last heading (#MyPage-Conclusions) without creating a anchor of my own but that would still break the Table of Contents plugin.

I suggest that either checking to make sure a specific anchor is unique within the page against a list generated while creating them. Adding a hash of the path wouldn't help if the Test Cases lacked their numbers. 
{noformat}

