  {panel}

I would like to have a Jira theme for Confluence, so that both site can be viewed with the same look. It is confusing for our user to have different look and feel. They expect have the two tools integrated (/doc suburl is assigned to confluence).
When you have both software it would also be nice to have links in the menu bar that link from Jira to Confluence and the other way round.
I did modify the layout in Confluence to have a similar header but I had to revert to the standard layouts after upgrading to 2.2.2 for compatibility problem. For this reason I do not want to modify the template just for integration, as this is something which is likely to be broken with every new release.

