  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6215].
  {panel}

In the "Create Template" or "Update Template" screens, there is no hint at all about whether or how one can enter variables into the template. I happen to know templates support variables, which is a great feature. A notation guide of the sort that appears when editing a page would be great for when editing a template as well. It should at least document template variables, and better yet, all the other page notation as well (since it can also be used within a page template).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6214].
  {panel}

In Admin: User  or Group Management, it would be very helpful to have a quick predictive text look up that would draw matching names from the user database as you begin to type a user or group name that you want to modify,

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6193].
  {panel}

Add View, Edit, Attachments, and Info tab at the bottom of the Confluence window.

It would save me time if I had these tabs at both the bottom and the top of pages I am editing.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6187].
