When using the default left hand navigation them, and go to administer a space's permissions, the page is too large to fit within a 1024 x 768 screen - causing the page to span out to the right hand side and inducing a horizontal scroll bar within the browser.

We should ensure that all pages render successfully within the 1024 x 768 standard when using our default themes (obviously we can't allow for all themes).

Now that themes are selected during space creation, this is becoming more important.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6180].
  {panel}

While email integration is offered at the space level, it is not available at the page level. Stephen Danelutti from netociety (one of our partners) has suggested this feature.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6175].
  {panel}

If you edit the location and then "Save" the page the location editor remains open on every successive page you edit. It took me weeks to work out that I could click the "Done" button to close the panel down. :-)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6174].
  {panel}

Although search terms are highlighted in the search results page, it would also be handy if the same matching terms were highlighted when viewing a page from the search results. (i.e. click on the page link, and the same search terms are highlighted in yellow on the page itself)

If you're searching for a particular term in a long document, it's much easier to find the word if it is already highlighted for you. (The Google Toolbar does this for Google searches - see http://johnbokma.com/firefox/google-toolbar-customizing.html for an example)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6172].
  {panel}

When searching for a user to give him a group it is not convenient to i	to differ between my.mail@company.de and My.Mail@Company.de or stefan baader and Stefan Baader. It's not useful.

Kind Regards
Stefan

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6164].
  {panel}

Regarding the optional hash in renderContent - it would be quite useful if the hash would include flags to disable wiki markup boxes such as the "tip" or "warning" boxes. Perhaps boolean hashes like "warn_box_on = 1"?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6150].
  {panel}

It would be so useful to be able to bulk download pages as *.wiki files, where the content is the regular wiki notation. Then you can get on a plane; hack the documentation to your hearts content and re-upload it all back again.

I'm aware of the XML download - but would so prefer using the directory layout for the parent/child relationships - and a plain text file for the wiki markup

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6145].
  {panel}

I've often got a page which includes another page, or a few other pages. (I sometimes tend to create a page which just includes another page when I wanna kinda do redirects if I decide to rename a page).

The View page looks great. When you click edit I can change the pages I link - but it'd be great to be able to just go straight to the edit screen of the pages that are included. i.e. its quite rare for me to edit the page which is a few includes - its common for me to want to edit the content that is being included.

e.g.  if there is a page like this

{include:Foo}
{include:Bar}

Then on the View screen - if pages are included, render a few links for the 'Edit Foo', 'Edit Bar' so that in 1 click I can edit one of the included pages

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-6109].
  {panel}

To extend the {include:page} macro to be able to only include a tagged section of a page.
This would make it possible to create a page which summarizes resourceplans for several projects


Example:
ProjectPage1
{section:name=abstract} Abstract for project 1 {section}
{section:name=resources} Table of all the resources planned for project 1 {section}

ProjectPage2
{section:name=abstract} Abstract for project 2 {section}
{section:name=resources} Table of all the resources planned for project 2 {section}

Summarypage
{include:ProjectPage1:resources}
{include:ProjectPage2:resources} 


Would result in

Summarypage
Table of all the resources planned for project 1
Table of all the resources planned for project 2

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
